						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of two silver vessels, a plate and a salver for holding the sacred offerings to the god and also of a fly-whisk with labelled golden handle and a gold cup <hi rend="italic">[koḷgai]</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Tiruvaḍigaḻ Aiyanaḍi</hi> [See. <hi rend="bold">Nos. 139</hi> and <hi rend="bold">189</hi> above] who is here called <hi rend="bold">Śembiyaṉ Vēśālippāḍi-Mūvēndavēḷāṉ.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
